The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                    Sunday , November 15 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                              NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Madurai, Nov. 14 (PTI): A government clerk who allegedly insulted two applicants at his office faces a police probe under a rare high court order.          
	Madras High Court today asked police to investigate a complaint by a lawyer who has accused a passport office employee of abusing him and his wife.          
	Observing that government staff are expected to be polite to the public, the court asked the police to register a first information report.          
	Petitioner Imam Hussain said he had visited the Madurai passport office with his wife on September 15. When the accused clerk refused to accept his bank passbook as proof of residence, he had taken the matter up with the passport officer. This angered the employee, who snatched the application, Hussain alleged.                   
	 Kochi (PTI): CISF personnel have seized a French yacht without valid documents near Kochi port. The owner of the yacht, Andrana, and a US national who were on board are being questioned. They said they had stopped near Kochi on their way to Madagascar because of rough weather.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): The CBI has arrested a central government official and his wife for allegedly amassing assets disproportionate to their known sources of income. The CBI had received graft complaints against V.K. Agarwal, an additional commissioner with the excise department, and his wife Prameela, a head clerk with the Central Railway.                  
	 Ahmedabad (PTI): A freedom fighter from Gujarat has approached state authorities alleging harassment by police. Santoshkumar Surendranath Saha, 87, claimed police officers had forcibly entered his home and accused him of being a Bangladeshi having terror links.                  
	 Ara (PTI): RJD chief Lalu Prasad on Saturday suffered bruises in his hands when a podium erected at Veer Kunwar Singh University, about 55km from here, to felicitate him, caved in. He had gone to the varsity to address a conference of his party workers.                                                                                                                                                               
